The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing metric spaces from data sampled around 1-dimensional filamentary structures, which can be seen as metric graphs. This involves techniques from computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS), as well as algorithms for computing distances between metric spaces (cs.DM) and approximating them (cs.GR). The paper also discusses applications in data analysis (cs.SI).
